\c 16
\s1 Pemberontakan Korah, Datan, Abiram dan On
\p
\v 1 Adalah seorang keturunan Kohat dari suku Lewi bernama Korah, anak dari Yishar, yang bersekongkol dengan Datan dan Abiram, keduanya anak-anak Eliab. Bersama dengan On, anak Pelet. Mereka bertiga berasal dari suku Ruben.
\v 2 Berempat bersama-sama mereka mengajak 250 orang dari antara pemimpin orang Israel untuk memberontak terhadap Musa.
\v 3 Mereka datang mencela Harun dan Musa. Mereka berkata, “Kalian berdua terlalu berlebihan menggunakan otoritas kalian. Seluruh masyarakat kita adalah orang kudus, dan TUHAN ada di tengah-tengah kita. Mengapa kalian meninggikan diri kalian di atas umat TUHAN?”
\p
\v 4 Ketika Musa mendengar perkataan mereka, tersungkurlah dia di atas tanah.
\v 5 Lalu berkatalah Musa kepada Korah dan teman-temannya, “Besok pagi TUHAN akan menunjukkan siapa yang TUHAN pilih sebagai imam-Nya, yang kudus dan yang boleh menghadap Dia. TUHAN hanya akan mengijinkan orang pilihannya mendekat kepada-Nya. 
\v 6 Jadi, Korah dan teman-temanmu, besok bawalah tempat pembakaran dupa,
\v 7 taruhlah bara dan kemenyan di dalamnya di hadapan TUHAN besok pagi, dan TUHAN akan menunjukkan orang pilihannya. Kalianlah yang menggunakan kuasa yang TUHAN berikan secara berlebihan, hai keturunan Lewi!”
\p
\v 8 Lanjut Musa kepada Korah, “Kalian para keturunan Lewi, dengarkan aku!
\v 9 Allah Israel sudah memisahkan kalian dari antara umat-Nya untuk melayani Dia di Kemah Suci dan melayani umat-Nya. Apakah kalian anggap itu hal yang sepele?
\v 10 TUHAN membawa kalian mendekat kepada-Nya, dan kalian ingin menjadi Imam juga?
\v 11 Sesungguhnya kepada TUHANlah kalian para keturunan Lewi memberontak, bukan terhadap Harun kalian memberontak.”
\p
\v 12 Lalu Musa memanggil Datan dan Abiram, anak-anak Eliab, tetapi mereka menolak datang menghadap Musa.
\v 13 Mereka mengirim pesan kepada Musa, “Engkau membawa kami keluar dari negeri Mesir, yang penuh dengan susu dan madu, ke gurun pasir untuk membunuh kami, bahkan sekarang engkau ingin menjadi penguasa atas kami, menurutmu itu hal sepele?
\v 14 Bahkan, engkau tidak memberikan kepada kami negeri yang berlimpah madu dan susu, tanah untuk ditanami gandum dan anggur. Engkau hanya menipu kami. Kami tidak akan datang menghadap engkau.”
\p
\v 15 Maka marahlah Musa, dan berserulah dia kepada TUHAN, “Janganlah terima persembahan mereka. Saya tidak pernah mengambil barang apapun dari mereka, bahkan seekor keledai pun tidak, dan tidak pernah menyakiti mereka.”
\p
\v 16 Berkatalah Musa kepada Korah, “Engkau dan mereka yang bersekutu dengan engkau haruslah datang kemari besok pagi dan berdiri di hadapan TUHAN. Harun juga akan datang menghadap bersama-sama dengan kalian.
\v 17 Setiap kalian akan membawa dupa dan kemenyan saat kalian datang menghadap TUHAN. Baik engkau, teman-temanmu yang dua ratus lima puluh orang itu dan juga Harun.”
\p
\v 18 Maka setiap mereka membawa dupa dan kemenyan dan berkumpul di depan pintu masuk tenda untuk berhadapan dengan Musa dan Harun.
\v 19 Kemudian Korah mengumpulkan semua orang yang mendukung dia dan menentang Musa. Dan kemuliaan TUHAN tampak di hapadapan kami semua,
\v 20 kemudian berkatalah TUHAN kepada Musan dan Harun,
\v 21 “Pisahkanlah diri kalian dari kumpulan ini, karena Aku akan menghukum mereka dengan segera!”
\p
\v 22 Tetapi Musa dan Harun jatuh bersujud dan berkata, “Allah pencipta segala yang hidup, apakah Engkau akan menghukup seluruh umat hanya karena kesalahan satu orang?”
\p
\v 23-24 Maka berkatalah TUHAN kepada Musa, “Jika demikian, katakan kepada yang lain untuk menyingkir dari kemah-kemah Korah, Datan dan Abiram.”
\p
\v 25 Maka berdirilah Musa dan pergi ke perkemahan Datan dan Abiram dengan para pemimpin Israel mengikuti dia.
\v 26 Berkatalah Musa kepada umat Israel, “Menjauhlah dari perkemahan orang-orang jahat ini, dan janganlah menyentuh apapun kepunyaan mereka, agar kalian tidak binasa bersama-sama dengan dosa mereka!”
\v 27 Maka umat Israel menjauh dari perkemahan Korah, Datan dan Abiram. Datan dan Abiram keluar dari kemah-kemah mereka bersama-sama dengan keluarga mereka, dan berdiri di depan pintu kemah mereka.
\p
\v 28 Musa berkata kepada mereka, “Bukan saya yang memutuskan melakukan segala hal yang sudah saya kerjakan. TUHANlah yang memilih saya dan mengutus saya untuk mengerjakan hal-hal itu. Dan sekarang TUHAN yang akan membuktikannya kepada kalian.
\v 29 If these men die in a normal way, then it will be clear that Yahweh did not choose me.
\v 30 But if Yahweh does something that has never happened before, if he causes the ground\add that is under their feet\add* to open up and swallow these men\add and their families\add* and all their possessions, and they fall into the opening and are buried while they are still alive, then you will know that these men have insulted Yahweh.”
\p
\v 31 As soon as Moses/I said this, the ground split open beneath those men.
\v 32 It swallowed those men and their families and all those who were standing there with Korah and all of their possessions.
\v 33 They fell into the opening in the ground while they were still alive, and all their possessions fell into the opening also. They disappeared, and the ground closed back up again.
\v 34 They screamed as they fell, and all the people who were standing nearby heard them scream. The people\add were terrified and\add* cried out as they ran away, saying,“\add We do not want\add* the ground to swallow us also!”
\p
\v 35 And then a fire from Yahweh came down \add from the sky\add* and burned up the 250 men who were burning the incense!
\p
\v 36 Then Yahweh said to Moses/me,
\v 37 “Tell Aaron's son Eleazar to take the pans that had incense in them away from the fire and to scatter the burning coals.The pans that those men \add were carrying\add* are ◄holy/dedicated to me►\add because they burned incense to me in them\add*.
\v 38 Those men have now died because of their sin; so \add Eleazarmust\add* take their pans and hammer the metal to make it become very thin. He must make a covering for the altar with that metal. Those pans were used to offer incense to me, so they are ◄holy/dedicated to me►.\add What happened to\add* those pans will now warn the Israeli people.”
\p
\v 39 So Eleazar the priest collected the 250 pans for burning incense that had been used by the men who died in the fire. He hammered the pans very thin to make a covering for the altar, as Yahweh told Moses/me should be done.
\v 40 That warned the Israeli people that only those who were descendants of Aaron were permitted to burn incense for an offering to Yahweh. If anyone else did that, the same thing that happened to Korah and those who were with him would happen to them.
\p
\v 41 But the following morning, all the Israeli people started to complain against Aaron and Moses/me, saying “You have killed many people who belonged to Yahweh!”
\p
\v 42 When all the people gathered together to protest about what Aaron and Moses/I had done, they looked at the Sacred Tent and saw that the sacred cloud had covered it, and the glory of Yahweh had appeared.
\v 43 Aaron and Moses/I went and stood in front of the Sacred Tent.
\v 44 Then Yahweh said to Moses/me,
\v 45 “Get away from these people, in order that I can get rid of them immediately\add without injuring you two\add*!” But Aaron and Moses/I prostrated themselves/ourselves on the ground\add and prayed\add*.
\p
\v 46 Moses/I said to Aaron, “Quickly take another pan and put in it some burning/hot coals from the altar. Put incense in the pan, and carry it out among the people to atone for the sins of the people. Yahweh is very angry with them, and\add I know that\add* a ◄severe plague/bad sickness► has already started among them.”
\v 47 So Aaron did what Moses/I told him. He took the burning incense out among the people. The plague had already started to strike the people, but Aaron continued to burn the incenseso that God would forgive them for the sins they had committed.
\v 48 He stood between the people who had already died and those who were still alive, and then the plague stopped.
\v 49 But 14,700 people had already died from that plague/sickness, in addition to the people who died with Korah.
\v 50 Then after the plague had ended, Aaron and Moses/I returned to the entrance of the Sacred Tent.